drift 
The boat drifted with the current.（船随水流漂流。）
The conversation drifted to politics.（谈话逐渐转向政治话题。）

detection 
Early detection of cancer is crucial.（早期发现癌症至关重要。）
Smoke detectors are for fire detection.（烟雾探测器用于火灾发现。）

simplify 
We need to simplify the process.（我们需要简化流程。）
The manual was simplified for beginners.（手册为初学者做了简化。）

conflict 
There is a conflict between the two teams.（两队之间有冲突。）
Her actions conflict with her words.（她的行为与言辞不一致。）

picky
He's very picky about food.（他对食物很挑剔。）
Don't be so picky about small details.（不要对小细节过于挑剔。）

roll
Roll the ball to me.（把球滚给我。）
She rolled the dough.（她擀面团。）
Let's roll out the new system next week.（下周推出新系统。）

invocation
The priest gave an invocation before the ceremony.（牧师在仪式前祈祷。）
Function invocation in programming calls the method.（编程中函数调用调用方法。）

legal 
They sought legal advice.（他们寻求法律建议。）
It's legal to park here.（这里停车是合法的。）

criteria
The selection criteria are clear.（选择标准很清楚。）
We need to set criteria for evaluating proposals.（我们需要制定评估提案的准则。）
Academic excellence is one of the main criteria for admission.（学术优秀是录取的主要标准之一。）

formal 
He wore a formal suit to the interview.（他穿着正式西装去面试。）
Formal approval is required for this process.（这个流程需要正式批准。）
A formal letter is better than an email in this case.（在这种情况下正式信件比电子邮件更合适。）

